Pull Apart Caramel Coffee Cake

Quarter each biscuit from 3 tubes refrigerated flaky buttermilk biscuits.  
Arrange evenly in a 10 inch fluted tube pan coated with cooking spray.  
Combine 1 cup brown sugar, Â½ cup heavy cream, and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; pour over biscuits.  
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.  
Cool for 5 minutes before inverting onto a platter.
